### GET GRADES
## Returns a list of grades.
## This is only a valid operation for students.
##
## Response Body (200 OK) - Array of grade objects, each containing:
##   - id          (UUID): Unique identifier of the grade
##   - student_id  (string): Unique identifier of the student
##   - value       (string): The grade (e.g 4.56)
##   - weight      (string): The weight of the grade (e.g. 0.5)
##   - date        (string): The date on which the grade was issued
##
## Responses:
##   200 OK - Returns array of GetGradeResponse objects
##   403 Forbidden - No active session
##   4000 Bad REquest - You are not a student
##   500 Internal Server Error - Database Query failed
GET {{BASE}}/grade
Accept: application/json


### CREATE A GRADE
## Creates a new grade an associate it with a student.
## Restricted to Local Admin, Admin or Teacher roles.
##
## Request Body:
##   - value         (float, required): Value of the grade (from 0.000 - 6.000)
##   - weight        (float, required): The weight of the grade (e.g. 1.000)
##   - date          (NaiveDate, required): The date of the grade
##   - student_id    (UUID, required): UUID of the student the grade belongs to
##   - grade_id     (UUID, optional): UUID of the grade
##   - description   (String, optional): A description of the grade
##
## Responses:
##   201 Created - Grade created successfully; returns the new grade ID
##   400 Bad Request - Missing required fields or invalid UUID format
##   401 Unauthorized - Insufficient permissions for this role
##   403 Forbidden - No active session
##   404 Not Found - Student doesn't exist
##   500 Internal Server Error - Database Query failed
##
# @name grade
POST {{BASE}}/grade
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json


{
    "value": "4.5",
    "weight": "1.0",
    "date": "2026-07-07",
	"student_id": "8b738857-dc34-47ac-87e8-bf694594a82c",
	"description": "Eine Testnote",
    "course_id": "df010b05-0fc5-46d1-a372-ce7c4443b9e6" 
}


### EDIT A GRADE
## Partially updates an existing grade identified by its UUID in the path.
## Only the fields provided in the request body will be updated (PATCH semantics).
## Restricted to Local Admin, Admin or Teacher roles.
##
## Path Parameter:
##   - {grade_id} (UUID): The UUID of the grade to update
##
## Request Body (all fields optional - only included fields are updated):
##   - value         (float, optional): Value of the grade (from 0.000 - 6.000)
##   - weight        (float, optional): The weight of the grade (e.g. 1.000)
##   - date          (NaiveDate, optional): The date of the grade
##   - student_id    (UUID, optional): UUID of the student the grade belongs to
##   - grade_id     (UUID, optional): UUID of the grade
##   - description   (String, optional): A description of the grade
##
## Responses:
##   200 OK - grade updated successfully; returns updated grade object
##   400 Bad Request - Invalid UUID format or malformed body
##   401 Unauthorized - Insufficient permissions for this role
##   403 Forbidden - No active session
##   404 Not Found - grade does not exist
##   500 Internal Server Error - Database Query failed
PATCH {{BASE}}/grade/{{grade.response.body.resource_id}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "description": "Vokabeltest"
}


### DELETE A GRADE
## Permanently deletes a grade identified by its UUID in the path.
## This action is irreversible. 
## Restricted to Local Admin, Admin and Teacher roles.
##
## Path Parameter:
##   - {grade_id} (UUID): The UUID of the grade to delete
##
## Responses:
##   200 OK - grade deleted successfully
##   401 Unauthorized - Insufficient permissions for this role
##   403 Forbidden - No active session
##   404 Not Found - grade UUID does not exist
DELETE {{BASE}}/grade/{{grade.response.body.resource_id}}
Accept: application/json